{"article_id":"ONWcoUQeqCcWTjvT","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Story highlights","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"The report cites `` management deficiencies '' at high levels of the State Department","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"It concludes","depth":10},{"id":3,"text":"`` there was no protest prior to the attacks '' on September 11","depth":10},{"id":4,"text":"Staffing for the Bureau of Diplomatic Security was `` inadequate , ''","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"report says","depth":10},{"id":6,"text":"An independent review of the September 11 attacks on the U.S. Consulate in Benghazi","depth":11},{"id":7,"text":"released Tuesday","depth":11},{"id":8,"text":"cited `` systemic failures and leadership and management deficiencies '' at the State Department .","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"The attacks killed four Americans ,","depth":11},{"id":10,"text":"including U.S . Ambassador J. Christopher Stevens","depth":11},{"id":11,"text":"The failures resulted in a security plan","depth":12},{"id":12,"text":"`` that was inadequate for Benghazi","depth":13},{"id":13,"text":"and grossly inadequate","depth":14},{"id":14,"text":"to deal with the attack","depth":15},{"id":15,"text":"that took place , ''","depth":15},{"id":16,"text":"the 39-page , unclassified version of the report concluded .","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"Veteran diplomat Thomas Pickering and former Joint Chiefs of Staff Chairman Adm. Mike Mullen , both members of the review board , are scheduled to brief members of the House Foreign Affairs and Senate Foreign Relations committees in private on Wednesday .","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"The board cited a lack of resources as at least partly to blame .","depth":5},{"id":19,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"Person detained in Benghazi attacks","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"Person detained in Benghazi attacks","depth":12},{"id":24,"text":"01:42","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"Discontent spreads over Benghazi response","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":13},{"id":29,"text":"Discontent spreads over Benghazi response","depth":13},{"id":30,"text":"03:39","depth":12},{"id":31,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"Susan Rice responds to Benghazi critics","depth":13},{"id":33,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":13},{"id":34,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":14},{"id":35,"text":"Susan Rice responds to Benghazi critics","depth":14},{"id":36,"text":"01:47","depth":13},{"id":37,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"FBI seeking Benghazi tips on Facebook","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":13},{"id":40,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":14},{"id":41,"text":"FBI seeking Benghazi tips on Facebook","depth":15},{"id":42,"text":"02:36","depth":15},{"id":43,"text":"`` The solution requires a more serious and sustained commitment from Congress","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"to support State Department needs , ''","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"it said .","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"The board found","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"that Washington tended `` to overemphasize the positive impact of physical security upgrades ...","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"while generally failing to meet Benghazi 's repeated requests ''","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"to beef up personnel .","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"The board completed its investigation this week","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"and sent a copy Monday to Secretary of State Hillary Clinton ,","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"who said in letters to the heads of those committees","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"that she accepted every one of its 24 recommendations .","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"They include strengthening security ,","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"adding fire-safety precautions","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"and improving intelligence collection in high-threat areas .","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"The report said","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"`` there was no protest prior to the attacks , ''","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"which it described as `` unanticipated in their scale and intensity . ''","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"It also cited the Bureau of Diplomatic Security staff as `` inadequate '' in Benghazi on the day of the attack and in the months and weeks","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"leading up to it ,","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"`` despite repeated requests from Special Mission Benghazi and Embassy Tripoli for additional staffing . ''","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"The report said","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"there had been a `` lack of transparency , responsiveness , and leadership at the senior levels '' in Washington , Tripoli and Benghazi .","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"`` Security in Benghazi was not recognized and implemented as a 'shared responsibility ' by the bureaus in Washington","depth":13},{"id":66,"text":"charged with supporting the post ,","depth":13},{"id":67,"text":"resulting in stove-piped discussions and decisions on policy and security , ''","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"it said .","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"`` That said ,","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"Embassy Tripoli did not demonstrate strong and sustained advocacy with Washington for increased security for Special Mission Benghazi . ''","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"The report said","depth":13},{"id":72,"text":"the short-term nature of the mission 's staff ,","depth":14},{"id":73,"text":"many of whom were inexperienced U.S. personnel , `` resulted in diminished institutional knowledge , continuity and mission capacity . ''","depth":14},{"id":74,"text":"The mission was also `` severely under-resourced with regard to certain needed security equipment , ''","depth":13},{"id":75,"text":"it said .","depth":13},{"id":76,"text":"It singled out for criticism the dependence on `` poorly skilled '' members of the Libyan February 17 Martyrs ' Brigade and unarmed local guards","depth":13},{"id":77,"text":"who were supposed to provide security .","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"It noted","depth":13},{"id":79,"text":"that , at the time of Stevens ' visit , militia members `` had stopped accompanying Special Mission vehicle movements in protest over salary and working hours . ''","depth":13},{"id":80,"text":"Though it said","depth":13},{"id":81,"text":"there had been no specific , credible threats on the day of the attack ,","depth":13},{"id":82,"text":"the significance of the anniversary of the 9/11 terror attacks in 2001 had led Stevens to decide to hold meetings on the compound on September 11 of this year .","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"But security systems and the Libyan response `` fell short ''","depth":12},{"id":84,"text":"when the compound came was penetrated `` by dozens of armed attackers . ''","depth":12},{"id":85,"text":"The report offers a detailed description","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"of what happened that night .","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"It said","depth":13},{"id":88,"text":"Libyan mission guards were not present ,","depth":14},{"id":89,"text":"local militia fled their posts","depth":15},{"id":90,"text":"and `` there simply was not enough time","depth":16},{"id":91,"text":"for armed U.S. military assets to have made a difference . ''","depth":16},{"id":92,"text":"The board said","depth":13},{"id":93,"text":"it could not determine","depth":15},{"id":94,"text":"how a gate at the compound was breached ,","depth":15},{"id":95,"text":"`` but the speed","depth":17},{"id":96,"text":"with which attackers entered","depth":17},{"id":97,"text":"raised the possibility ''","depth":16},{"id":98,"text":"that the guards had left it open .","depth":15},{"id":99,"text":"Eric Boswell , assistant secretary of state for diplomatic security , and Charlene Lamb , deputy assistant secretary of state for international programs , oversaw decisions on security at the diplomatic outpost .","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"Lamb testified before Congress about the security precautions .","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"Documents show","depth":13},{"id":102,"text":"Lamb denied repeated requests for additional security in Libya .","depth":13},{"id":103,"text":"Despite all the criticism ,","depth":7},{"id":104,"text":"the board found","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"no U.S. government employee had engaged in misconduct or ignored responsibilities","depth":9},{"id":106,"text":"and did not recommend","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"any individual be disciplined .","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"Clinton ,","depth":7},{"id":109,"text":"who is recovering from a stomach virus and concussion ,","depth":7},{"id":110,"text":"ordered the review in the aftermath of the attack .","depth":6},{"id":111,"text":"Such reports are mandated by Congress","depth":6},{"id":112,"text":"when Americans","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"working on behalf of the U.S. government","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"are killed overseas .","depth":7},{"id":115,"text":"A notice","depth":7},{"id":116,"text":"sent to State Department employees","depth":7},{"id":117,"text":"said","depth":6},{"id":118,"text":"the implementation team had met Tuesday","depth":6},{"id":119,"text":"and would continue to do so regularly","depth":7},{"id":120,"text":"to carry out the board 's recommendations .","depth":7},{"id":121,"text":"The politics","depth":5},{"id":122,"text":"surrounding the events","depth":6},{"id":123,"text":"that led to the report","depth":6},{"id":124,"text":"have claimed one political casualty ,","depth":4},{"id":125,"text":"with Susan Rice , U.S. ambassador to the United Nations , last week pulling her name from consideration","depth":5},{"id":126,"text":"to succeed Clinton .","depth":5},{"id":127,"text":"Some Republican senators had said","depth":5},{"id":128,"text":"they would put a hold on her nomination","depth":7},{"id":129,"text":"if President Barack Obama had submitted it ,","depth":7},{"id":130,"text":"based on comments","depth":7},{"id":131,"text":"Rice made in the days after the attack .","depth":7},{"id":132,"text":"In place of Clinton , Deputy Secretaries of State William Burns and Thomas Nides will testify before the House and Senate committees Thursday .","depth":2}],"relations":[{"parent":265,"left":253,"right":264,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":253,"left":0,"right":252,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":252,"left":239,"right":251,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":239,"left":150,"right":238,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":150,"left":149,"right":18,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":149,"left":148,"right":17,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":148,"left":1,"right":147,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":147,"left":136,"right":146,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":136,"left":134,"right":135,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":134,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":135,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":146,"left":138,"right":145,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":138,"left":137,"right":8,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":137,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":145,"left":139,"right":144,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":139,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":144,"left":143,"right":16,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":143,"left":11,"right":142,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":142,"left":12,"right":141,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":141,"left":13,"right":140,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":140,"left":14,"right":15,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":238,"left":187,"right":237,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":187,"left":180,"right":186,"rela